 political dissent in present-day India, both irrevocably shaped conversations and critiques in the colonial public sphere and continues to influence anti-colonialism and postcolonial relationships between the state and the public. Disaffected draws out the coercive and emotional subtexts of law, literature, and cultural relationships, demonstrating how the criminalization of political alienation and dissent has shaped literary form and the political imagination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCensorshipzIndiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aCensorshipzIndiaxHistoryy20h century. 0aPolitical alienationzIndiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aPolitical alienationzIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitics and culturezIndiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aPolitics and culturezIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSeditionxLaw and legislationzIndia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh  aIndian penal code, Imperial Law, Affect and empire, Censorship and empire, Law and literature.  aSection124a.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishz978311075409408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021z9783110753868oZDB-23-DGC0 cprintz978150175387940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501753909?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501753909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501753909/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete